										<footer class="article-contributor contributors">
									

<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Cheryl Strayed</span></strong> is the author of the memoir&nbsp;<em>Wild</em>. Her essays have appeared in the <em>Best American Essays</em> series as well as&nbsp;the <em>New York Times</em>, <em>Washington Post Magazine</em>, <em>Vogue</em>, <em>Salon</em>, <em>Tin House</em>, and elsewhere. She is the co-host of the podcast <em>Dear Sugars</em>, which originated with her popular Dear Sugar advice column on <em><a href="http://therumpus.net/sections/dear-sugar/">The Rumpus</a></em>. She lives in Portland, Oregon.</p><a href="/contributors/cheryl-strayed" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


